title.59: The Punisher: Assassins' Guild Graphic Novel (1988) #1

description.4: The X-Men finally break free of Mesmero's wiles, but no sooner have they claimed victory, they are beset upon yet again - by MAGNETO! This fight, however, goes somewhat differently...for when the dust settles, the last man standing is MAGNETO TRIUMPHANT!
description.5: Daredevil takes toxic chemicals blinding children personally and he’s on the hunt to take down those responsible!
description.6: Here it is! Your #1 cover! And it looks like Wolverine and the Hulk are about to go at it again. Could it have ended any other way? These two have had so many epic brawls throughout the years they were bound to meet up again in the Top Covers competition. Todd McFarlane makes the fury palpable between the two sparring partners and heaven help anyone who gets in their way.
description.11: Cosmic rays have turned Ms. Marvel into...a Thing! And they've turned Thing into...even MORE of a Thing! How will they deal with their new mutations? Perhaps they'll need the help of an old friend- Black Panther!
description.17: Trickshot goads Hawkeye into following him to Paris where he meets the feet of Batroc the Leaper and Batroc's Brigade!  Plus, will Moon Knight accept an offer to lead his own team or will he continue on as a lone wolf?
description.19: Ed Marks heads stateside! Will he find home to be just as he left it?
description.20: Dr. Octopus has busted out of the mental hospital to destroy Spider-Man once and for all- by nuking New York City! The Doctor figures he's bound to kill his fearsome foe for sure that way!
description.21: Together the Super-Adaptoid and Machine Man reactivate Sentry 459. By the time the Avengers learn of the reactivation, it's far too late! Plus, Dr. Druid and the Black Knight have an unsettling discovery.
description.22: The new Captain America and Bucky are after the villainous Professor Power - and the villain may not survive the arrest! Meanwhile, the Captain and his allies are in jail- for helping the police fight the all-new Serpent Society!
description.24: It's the wild wrap-up of the Evolutionary War! But who's going to fight it, considering the Avengers have disbanded?
description.25: The West Coast Avengers take on Scorpio and his deadly android allies - the Zodiac!
description.33: Ken Connell makes the grand gesture to convince the public Star Brand is a super hero….by bringing President Ronald Reagan the Apollo 11 shuttle! Meanwhile, what exciting news awaits Debbie?
description.34: Kree forces invade the peaceful planet of Zenn-La. Can Surfer, Mantis and Shalla Bal prevent the coming onslaught? Surfer must reconcile his feelings for Mantis, all while striking an agreement with the Kree’s Supreme Intelligence!
description.35: Matt Murdock is doing what he can to seek justice for those affected by Kelco’s chemical spills, but things get complicated when an assassin enters the picture!
description.37: Bruce Banner, Rick Jones, and Clay Quartermain have made it to Boulder, Colorado when Clay decides to confront Banner about his past.
description.38: The Evolutionary War Part 4. The New Mutants join the battle against the High Evolutionary - and one of the New Mutants gains a whole new set of powers!
description.43: To defeat Fasaud's evil plot, the Thing and Ms. Marvel travel all the way into outer space! But what horrible price will they pay to end his madness once and for all?
description.47: With Havok in danger, the Beast seeks out his old allies, the X-Men, to rescue him - unwittingly walking them all into a mesmerizing trap!
description.48: The last time we saw Doctor Octopus, he'd been driven insane by his obsession with Spider-Man. But when a guy has super-strong metal tentacles, can any asylum hold him for long?
description.49: The Avengers deactivate the Awesome Android, but not before they receive a distress call from the Fixer's former ally, Mentallo. The team discovers that it was Super-Adaptoid, and not Fixer, who activated the Awesome Android.
description.50: Nomad, the Falcon, and D-Man finally track down Steve Rogers and convince him to get back into costume- but it's not the Captain America costume!
description.60: Delve into the history of Hawkeye…what secrets are unearthed?  Plus, the villainy of Trickshot and the heroism of Monica Rambeau, Captain Marvel!
description.63: A man named Clark spins a yarn or two about 'Nam and WWII -- but some of these stories may be fables!
description.67: Frank Gibbs commits his wife to a mental institution to keep his connection to the underworld a secret. Spider-Man investigates to discover the truth.
description.68: PETER PARKER FINALLY ESCAPES FROM THE KINGPIN'S MENTAL HOSPITAL! Life in the Mad Dog Ward finally comes to a close. And Peter can't leave without getting past Brainstorm!
description.69: As the Kree/Skrull war rages on, Silver Surfer and Mantis uncover the Elders’ plot against Galactus. A defeated Obliterator says far too much. And when Norrin’s home world of Zenn-La is threatened with imminent war, Silver Surfer must answer the call!
description.70: The West Coast Avengers' war against Scorpio swings into high gear!
description.77: The X-Men return to Earth and take a much needed vacation - until WEAPON ALPHA strikes! Who is this Canadian superhuman, and why is he after the X-Men - or more specifically, WOLVERINE?
description.78: The Man Without Fear versus Wolverine of the X-Men! Get ready for a brawl like none other.
description.79: Bruce Banner, Rick Jones, and Clay Quartermain are on the run from SHIELD.
description.80: God against god! Thor may be a Norse god, but this day he battles the mighty Leir, of the pantheon of Celtic gods! But can even their combined might defeat the mysterious griffin creature that attacks them both?
description.83: The fight against Fasaud continues! While Johnny and Crystal take on the electronic menace at home, Ben and Ms. Marvel take the fight to Fasaud's home turf! But are they walking into a trap?
description.85: What would you do if you were Spider-Man but nobody believed you? Peter Parker's going to have to find the answer if he's ever going to get out of the Kingpin's insane asylum in "Mad Dogs"!
description.86: Dr. Druid snoops on his teammates in his astral form. While Druid finds all-too-personal information on his team, the Avengers square off against the Awesome Android! The Fixer manages to escape!
description.87: After three months among the missing, Steve Rogers is back! But he may regret it when he meets the ecological terrorist Brother Nature! What will Steve do now that he's no longer Captain America? Will his friends, the Falcon, Nomad, and D-Man be able to help him?
description.89: Marks confronts the horrifying effects of chemical warfare firsthand!
description.90: Hawkeye has a blast from the past as he joins the circus again…only to find a villain also from his past!  Plus, Mockingbird in action!
description.93: The GLADIATOR has waged an all-out war on the Soviet Union! Can Star Brand stop him and save the greater good of the world from a potential WW3?! Meanwhile, Ken learns more truths about his origins- a little more than he expected…
description.94: The police are on to Kraven as they discover evidence leading to his lie...
description.95: Out of the frying pan…and into a new galactic battle! Mantis and Surfer may have escaped the Elders of the Universe, but how will they fare against The Obliterator? Spurred by the threat of death, Surfer displays the incredible Power Cosmic!
description.96: At last, it's the all-out final battle between the human and android versions of the criminal Zodiac cartel!

3.text: FALL OF THE MUTANTS tie-in! Power Pack is attacked by the Horsemen of Apocalypse! Guest-starring X-Factor!

6.text: After the Hulk accidentally destroys a plane, Wolverine is out to make him pay for his mistake. It's Wolverine vs. the Hulk!

Here it is!  Your #1 cover!  And it looks like Wolverine and the Hulk are about to go at it again.  Could it have ended any other way?  These two have had so many epic brawls throughout the years they were bound to meet up again in the Top Covers competition.  Todd McFarlane makes the fury palpable between the two sparring partners and heaven help anyone who gets in their way.

9.text: Apocalypse’s Ship and Horsemen are destroying New York City; X-Force responds with full force.

12.text: With each team holding members of the other team captive, the X-Men and the Freedom Force are at an uneasy stalemate. But when the Adversary's chaos begins tearing Dallas asunder, the two teams must cooperate to save the innocent-and themselves!

13.text: ELECTRO HAS WON! Even if Spider-Man survives, how can he beat a foe that knows exactly how to beat HIM?

14.text: They were transformed into Earth's greatest heroes - knowing that they would die within twelve months as a fatal side-effect. Now one of the Morituri, Radian, has a chance to find a cure for the terminal consequences. But his quest for that cure may cut the lives of hiss teammates even shorter when he leads them into a trap set by a band of super-powered alien Hordians!

15.text: An atomic plot sets the Punisher on a global course in “Garbage”! But first, Castle must prevent nuclear fallout in New Jersey!

18.text: Rusty, Skids, Boom-Boom, Rictor and Taki hatch a daring plan to rescue Artie and Leech from N'astirh, demon of Limbo. But they can't do it without X-Factor's help. Will the mutant superheroes answer the call?

Rusty, Skids, Boom-Boom, Rictor and Taki hatch a daring plan to rescue Artie and Leech from N'astirh, demon of Limbo. But they can't do it without X-Factor's help. Will the mutant superheroes answer the call?

24.text: It's the wild wrap-up of the Evolutionary War! But who's going to fight it, considering the Avengers have disbanded?

25.text: The West Coast Avengers take on Scorpio and his deadly android allies - the Zodiac!

26.text: A tale of the Warriors Three! Fandral the Dashing embarks on a Homeric quest told in the Mighty Marvel Manner! And he still finds time to woo many a maiden!

31.text: Iron Man goes rogue, so Tony Stark fires him! But wait, aren't they the same person? As Armor Wars continues, Iron Man reclaims Stark's technology in a deadly battle with the villainous Raiders -- but when he attacks scientist and hero Stingray, public opinion of the Golden Avenger falls lower than ever! How will Stark get out of this one?

32.text: In order to save Bird-Brain and his fellow Animates from the Animator, the New Mutants must take part in his cruel tests! Will the team make it off the Animator's island?

33.text: Ken Connell makes the grand gesture to convince the public Star Brand is a super hero….by bringing President Ronald Reagan the Apollo 11 shuttle! Meanwhile, what exciting news awaits Debbie?

34.text: Kree forces invade the peaceful planet of Zenn-La. Can Surfer, Mantis and Shalla Bal prevent the coming onslaught? Surfer must reconcile his feelings for Mantis, all while striking an agreement with the Kree’s Supreme Intelligence!

36.text: Crystal of the Inhumans…apprehended by her own family! The High Evolutionary “greets” the FF in Attilan, while Crystal has a tense one-on-one with King Black Bolt!

40.text: Will Apocalypse finally make X-Factor join his side?

41.text: The Savage Land has been decimated! The X-Men and High Evolutionary have a huge project ahead of them…but of course Garrok has to make things even more difficult, right?

44.text: While the X-Men search for Storm in Dallas, the government-sanctioned Freedom Force attempt to arrest them. The X-Men take refuge in Forge's penthouse...but Destiny predicts that by dawn, anyone in that building will be dead!

45.text: The origin of the Sin Eater is revealed! And the unthinkable happens -- Spider-Man falls in battle!

46.text: Meet the hottest new hero in the Marvel Universe - Speedball, the Masked Marvel! He's got to help Spider-Man and Daredevil stop the Kingpin's implacable drive to increase the supply of illegal drugs in New York City! Plus: a special fact-filled featured on Speedball!

51.text: A family is taken hostage by one of the Horde. But the Morituri can't rescue them - they're too busy standing trial for treason!

52.text: It’s Silver Surfer Vs. the ever-shifting Super Skrull in this Evolutionary Wars crossover issue!

53.text: The “Rev” may have an arsenal, but he can’t account for the one man army that’s Frank Castle! Punisher takes on a dangerous cult leader in the "Ministry of Death”!

54.text: Look out! Here come the High Evolutionary's Eliminators! They're under orders to destroy all the drug fields in South America - and they've got more than enough power to do it! You'd think the Punisher would be overjoyed! But these "allies" could be more dangerous than even his greatest enemy! The Punisher must decide - should he join them, or try to stop them! Plus: More secrets of the High Evolutionary are revealed!

55.text: Peter Parker went to Miami expecting to do a run-of-the-mill signing for his new book. But when the High Evolutionary strikes, Spidey must join forces with the misshapen Man-Thing and Miami's newest super hero, Poison, to protect not only the universe but all of the alternate universes as well!

56.text: Learn about the vigilante’s origin here! But beware -- that knowledge may prove deadly!

57.text: Madripoor frequenter Wolverine shares his knowledge on the world’s seediest port town with X-Factor and the New Mutants! Speedball learns that the villain Crooked Face has it out for his family! The Hulk may step into the role as Damage Control’s new spokesperson!

59.text: Frank Castle joins a cult of assassins to take down an inhumane crime boss!

62.text: The X-Terminators have been separated and placed in several different institutions. But when things go terribly wrong and Rusty is in need of a prison break, will his friends be around to help? Not if they can't help themselves out first!

The X-Terminators have been separated and placed in several different institutions. But when things go terribly wrong and Rusty is in need of a prison break, will his friends be around to help? Not if they can't help themselves out first!

64.text: Members of X-Force all receive the same distress call! Jean decides to lead the investigation.

65.text: Iron Man declares war! Criminals are using Tony Stark's technology for evil purposes, and Stark won't stand for it anymore! It's one of the most famous Iron Man stories of all time, and it all starts here! Featuring Ant-Man and Cassie Lang (the future Stature of the Young Avengers), and the threats of Stilt-Man and the Controller!

66.text: The New Mutants struggle to teach Bird-Brain how to act like a New Mutant, much less a human. Who are Bird-Brain's "friends," and how did he really come to be?

67.text: Frank Gibbs commits his wife to a mental institution to keep his connection to the underworld a secret. Spider-Man investigates to discover the truth.

68.text: PETER PARKER FINALLY ESCAPES FROM THE KINGPIN'S MENTAL HOSPITAL! Life in the Mad Dog Ward finally comes to a close. And Peter can't leave without getting past Brainstorm!

69.text: As the Kree/Skrull war rages on, Silver Surfer and Mantis uncover the Elders’ plot against Galactus. A defeated Obliterator says far too much. And when Norrin’s home world of Zenn-La is threatened with imminent war, Silver Surfer must answer the call!

70.text: The West Coast Avengers' war against Scorpio swings into high gear!

71.text: Introducing Stratosfire, Roxxon Oil’s own super heroine! But when Tony Stark uncovers Stratosfire’s true ties to Roxxon, will he be able to stop her before she takes down the oil corporation’s next rival? And how much does Stratosfire really know about her employer? Iron Man meets his match, and he’s not happy about it!

75.text: When Tony Stark is willing to sell one of his latest inventions, Nick Fury and S.H.I.E.L.D. attempt to intervene.  But what could be so dangerous and what will Tony do to make sure the world is safe from one of his creations?  Of course, he'll have to suit up as Iron Man to do so.

84.text: Storm's reckoning with Forge is finally at hand! But has Forge been working for the evil Adversary or against him!

88.text: It's the first and second generation Morituri square off against their third generation counterparts! The squads are locked in battle, but a stranger in a very familiar uniform makes his presence known. Who could this warrior be?

92.text: The team has fun taking Bird Boy out to the mall, but what does Magma transferring to the White Queen's Massachusetts Academy mean for the New Mutants and the Hellions?

93.text: The GLADIATOR has waged an all-out war on the Soviet Union! Can Star Brand stop him and save the greater good of the world from a potential WW3?! Meanwhile, Ken learns more truths about his origins- a little more than he expected…

94.text: The police are on to Kraven as they discover evidence leading to his lie...

95.text: Out of the frying pan…and into a new galactic battle! Mantis and Surfer may have escaped the Elders of the Universe, but how will they fare against The Obliterator? Spurred by the threat of death, Surfer displays the incredible Power Cosmic!

96.text: At last, it's the all-out final battle between the human and android versions of the criminal Zodiac cartel!

97.text: A tale of the Warriors Three! Hogun the Grim has a humorless run-in with a Bridge Troll…and must later collect a groom-turned-goat before his nuptial hour’s at hand!
